allergy  noun [C]
the condition of reacting badly to something, such as milk, the fur of particular animals or dust, causing someone who eats it, touches it or breathes it in to feel uncomfortable or become ill, although it is harmless to most people.
Your skin problems are caused by an allergy to wheat.

allergic  adjective
I'm allergic to cats./I have an allergic reaction to cats.
(figurative informal) My Dad's allergic to (= he hates) pop music.
